						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Stone near the ruined fort.</hi></p>						

						<p>Tipu Sultān.</p>						

						<p>This record of the <hi rend="bold">18th Century A.D.</hi> states that under the orders of <hi rend="bold">Tipu Sultān,</hi> the village of <hi rend="bold">Chennāpura,</hi> in the <hi rend="bold">Rāṇebennūr</hi> (division) was granted as <hi rend="italic">sarvamānya</hi> to a <hi rend="italic">Jūḍidār</hi> (name not specified) after receiving from him ninety <hi rend="italic">varāhas.</hi> The date of the record is <hi rend="bold">Parābhava, Mārgaśira.</hi></p>						

						<p>The Sun, the Crescent of the Moon and some Urdu letters are engraved at the top. </p>						

						</summary>
